<span class="txth1">color_peruse : Peruse, compare, choose color schemes</span> 

<br>
<br>

<!-- karma table -->
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="1" bordercolor="#000066">
<tr>
  <td class="lightbg"><b>&nbsp;script karma&nbsp;</b></td>
  <td>
    Rating <b>7/4</b>,
    Downloaded by 508  </td>
  <td class="lightbg">
  <b>&nbsp;Comments, bugs, improvements&nbsp;</b>
  </td>
  <td>
    <a href="http://vim.wikia.com/wiki/Script:1607">Vim wiki</a>
  </td>  
</tr>
</table>
<p>

<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0">
<tr><td class="prompt">created by</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="/account/profile.php?user_id=10303">Walter Hutchins</a></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">script type</td></tr>
<tr><td>utility</td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">description</td></tr>
<tr><td>Peruse, compare, choose color schemes<br><br>When the cursor is in the ColorPeruse window:&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>&lt;kPlus&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;:ColorPeruse 1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (next color)<br>&lt;kMinus&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;:ColorPeruse -1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(prev color)<br>&lt;kMultiply&gt; :ColorPeruse&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (original color)<br>&lt;kDivide&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp; :ColorPeruse 0&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(color under cursor)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; :call ColorPeruseDel() (remove duplicate lines)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; +&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; :call ColorPeruseMerge() (append all :set rtp colors to list)<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Help<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; :q&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; quit<br> <br><br>You are in vim when in the ColorPeruse window, so you can edit items you <br>don't like from the list, or place markers to return to re-view particular colorschemes.<br>You can cut/paste to put favorites or color/lightness groups together <br>to compare more closely.<br>Also, since it is in vim, you can save the ColorPeruse list to a file, or <br>load it from a previous perusal list.<br><br><br></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
<tr><td class="prompt">install details</td></tr>
<tr><td>copy to ~/.vim/plugin<br><br>Put this mapping in .vimrc:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;map &lt;Leader&gt;cp :ColorPeruse&lt;Space&gt;Mylist&lt;CR&gt;:echo g:colors_name&lt;CR&gt;<br>Then \cp will start it up.<br>If you once create this 'Mylist' file, it is suggested that you move it<br>into a directory in vim's runtimepath. Type :set rtp to see this path.<br>This 'Mylist' file does not have to exist.<br>In such a list, you may have comments beginning with &quot; which will be ignored,<br>and you can sort the list in any order you choose.<br><br><br></td></tr>
<tr><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
</table>

